Western Australia spans the western third of the country and is made up mostly of the arid Outback. Can you identify all 107 of these local government areas (LGAs) of Western Australia? The state's population is concentrated in its fertile southwest corner, home to the Margaret River wine region and the capital city of Perth. The Shire of Ashburton is named for the Ashburton River. Exmouth is situated at the tip of the North West Cape. Launceston is a densely populated area and one of the largest inland cities in Australia. If you learn a few interesting details about Western Australia and work with this map quiz, you'll be able to identify all these places in no time.

Seterra is an entertaining and educational geography game that lets you explore the world and learn about its countries, capitals, flags, oceans, lakes and more! You can access the Seterra online quiz site using your computer, phone, or tablet running the latest version of most web browsers, including Safari, Firefox, Chrome, and Internet Explorer.

There’s also a Seterra app that runs on iOS and Android phones and tablets! The Seterra app offers two game modes, plus high score lists to keep track of your progress. Also, with the app, you can play offline!
